China’s Energy-Savings Sales May Reach 500 Bln Yuan, 21st Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-06-30T02:23:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/china-s-energy-savings-sales-may-reach-500-bln-yuan-21st-says.html
China ’s energy-savings services
industry may reach sales of as much as 500 billion yuan, the
21st Century Business Herald reported, citing Xie Ji, deputy
director of the environment and resources department at the
National Development and Reform Commission.  The government will release a plan for the energy-saving
and environmental-protection industries “soon”, the newspaper
cited Xie as saying.  China has asked provinces and cities to cut energy
consumption per unit of gross domestic product by 16 percent,
the newspaper reported Xie as saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gregory Turk at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  